.TH _SIMPLE_SHELL 1 simple_shell\-0.1
.SH NAME
simple_shell - receive input from user to perfrom basic system calls.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include\ "main.h"

.B Interactive Mode: ./hsh

.B Non-Interactive Mode: [COMMAND]... | ./hsh
.P
.SH COMPILE
 gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
Our simple_shell program is capable of receiving input by the user at the command line. The program reads, splits, and executes line being provided.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B Receive system calls without any arguments, such as;

Example - |  ls | pwd | help | cd 




.B Receive system cals WITH arguments, such as;

Example - | ls -la | cd .. | mkdir ...[DIRECTORY] 




.B Handle PATHs for present files, such as;

Example - | realpath ...[FILE] 




.B 'exit' built-in operation available;

Example - | exit




.B 'env' built-in operation available;

Example - | env



.SH RETURN
 Returns commands being call by the user.
.SH BUGS
 The program currently goes on a infinite loop when initializing non-interactive.
.SH AUTHOR
 Giovanni Carmona | Jose Nieves | Christian Rosario
